The NCCN Guidelines for Palliative Care provide interdisciplinary 
recommendations on palliative care for patients with cancer. These NCCN 
Guidelines Insights summarize and provide context for the updated guidelines 
recommendations regarding hospice and end-of-life (EOL) care. Updates for 2017 
include revisions to and restructuring of the algorithms that address important 
EOL concerns. These recommendations were revised to provide clearer guidance for 
oncologists as they care for patients with cancer who are approaching the 
transition to EOL care. Recommendations for interventions and reassessment based 
on estimated life expectancy were streamlined and reprioritized to promote 
hospice referrals and improved EOL care.

