During epithelial tube morphogenesis, linear arrays of cells are converted into 
tubular structures through actomyosin-generated intracellular forces that induce 
tissue invagination and lumen formation. We have investigated lumen 
morphogenesis in the C. elegans vulva. The first discernible event initiating 
lumen formation is the apical constriction of the two innermost primary cells 
